mxCell.value: <font style="font-size: 48px; line-height: 1;">All aboard the Research Train!</font>

Research Train is a collaboration between Griffith University Library, Griffith University Research Methods Advisors (GURMA), the Office for Research (OfR) and eResearch Services. Workshops listed here are delivered through the OfR's Research Education and Development (RED) program or though GURMA. Workshop information may change as different providers update the services that they offer. Find out more and book a place at griffith.edu.au/research/research-services. Send feedback on this design to y.banens@griffith.edu.au.

<font style="font-size: 12px;">Station markers represent workshops available to researchers at Griffith University. Each line represents a domain of research skill, such as writing or statistics. Zones progress outwards from Zone 1 (Central Concepts) all the way to Zone 7 (Publication). Choose a line and see where it takes you!</font>
